cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper deals with the problem of cross-view matching for localizing ground vehicles using aerial perception. The paper discusses the use of deep learning methods for cross-view matching and evaluates the performance of the method using a city-wide dataset. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is computer vision (cs.CV), followed by robotics (cs.RO) as the paper deals with localization of ground vehicles. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques, which makes it relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the method using a photorealistic simulation, which makes it relevant to the sub-category of graphics (cs.GR).
